<subSubSection lastPageId="19" lastPageNumber="716" pageId="18" pageNumber="715" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="18.[806,1421,1820,1903]" lastBlockId="19.[164,779,198,1322]" lastPageId="19" lastPageNumber="716" pageId="18" pageNumber="715">
<emphasis box="[806,877,1820,1841]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="715">Adult:</emphasis>
Male 
<typeStatus box="[973,1073,1820,1842]" pageId="18" pageNumber="715">holotype</typeStatus>
: face with lateral margins inflated and indented slightly from just above margin of mouth so lower part of face appears as a narrow projection (view from in front). Face yellow and black haired with indistinct tubercle. Black mid-dorsal vitta present and not reaching the base of the antenna. Lateral vittae black, indistinct at eye and genae dark (
<figureCitation box="[239,305,320,342]" captionStart="Figures 5–7" captionStartId="37.[164,254,1372,1391]" captionTargetBox="[387,1219,196,1339]" captionTargetId="figure-0@37.[387,1221,196,1341]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="Figures 5–7. Adult Copestylum, lateral view of the head; scale bar = 2 mm. 5, Copestylum cochabamba sp. nov., male holotype; 6, Copestylum milae sp. nov., male holotype; 7, Copestylum hidalgense sp. nov., male holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5443482" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5443482/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="716">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Frons and ocellar triangle black and black haired. Antenna black with plumose arista. Basoflagellomere slightly excavated dorsally and twice as long as broad. Eyes with long black hairs reaching lower margin and facets of equal size. Ground colour of mesonotum black except for pale yellow lateral margins and posterior margin with a pair of pale yellow, rounded spots. Mesonotum with long, dark hairs and a pair of dusted stripes dorsocentrally ending just beyond the transverse suture. Scutellum yellow with black hairs. Pleurae black except for yellow posterior anepisternum and with long white hairs. Wing membrane hyaline with medial crossveins brown forming two central dark spots. Legs brown with tibiae pale at base and black haired. Abdominal sternites mainly yellow with a black medial spot on sternite 2 and the posterior margins of the sternites 3 and 4 with complete black bands wider in the centre. Sternite 2 pale haired and hairs on sternites 3 and 4 yellow except black where the integument is black. Tergite 1 completely black, tergites 2–4 yellow except for their posterior margins which have complete black bands and a black medial line. Anteriorly tergites yellow haired and posteriorly with short, black, reclined hairs. Tergite 4 with longer pale hairs. Genitalia: epandrium wider than tall in lateral view; surstylus short, irregularly rounded and with a dorsal tuft of long, black setae. Hypandrium indented deeply on the upper outer margin at the base of the superior lobe. Superior lobe elongate, almost as long as hypandrium and rounded not hooked apically. Aedeagus rounded apically (
<figureCitation box="[172,302,1299,1322]" captionStart="Figures 16–19" captionStartId="40.[144,234,1220,1239]" captionTargetBox="[367,1199,194,1190]" captionTargetId="figure-0@40.[367,1201,194,1190]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="Figures 16–19. Adult Copestylum, male genitalia; scale bar = 0.30 mm. 16–19, Copestylum milae sp. nov., male holotype: 16, genitalia and associated structures, lateral view; 17, hypandrium, ventral view. 18–19, Copestylum hidalgense sp. nov., male holotype: 18, genitalia and associated structures, lateral view; 19, hypandrium, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5443490" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5443490/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="716">Figs 18, 19</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[164,382,1381,1403]" box="[164,382,1381,1403]" pageId="19" pageNumber="716">
