<paragraph blockId="19.[826,1442,478,929]" pageId="19" pageNumber="716">
<emphasis box="[826,1027,479,500]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="716">Taxonomic notes:</emphasis>
This species is distinctive among species of the Apiciferum group and can be separated easily by the following characters: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Maier" authorityYear="2009" box="[1220,1374,540,561]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="716" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hidalgense">
<emphasis box="[1220,1374,540,561]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="716">C. hidalgense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a black flagellomere and eye hairs, these being yellow in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Maier" authorityYear="2009" box="[863,966,601,622]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="716" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="milae">
<emphasis box="[863,966,601,622]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="716">C. milae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Williston" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[987,1155,601,622]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="716" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadratum">
<emphasis box="[987,1155,601,622]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="716">C. quadratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Townsend" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[1233,1395,601,622]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="716" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apiciferum">
<emphasis box="[1233,1395,601,622]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="716">C. apiciferum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Maier" authorityYear="2009" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="716" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hidalgense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="716">C. hidalgense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the abdominal tergites mainly yellow with conspicuous black stripes but 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Maier" authorityYear="2009" box="[1284,1390,662,683]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="716" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="milae">
<emphasis box="[1284,1390,662,683]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="716">C. milae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Williston" baseAuthorityYear="1891" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="716" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadratum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="716">C. quadratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Townsend" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[1020,1180,693,714]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="716" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apiciferum">
<emphasis box="[1020,1180,693,714]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="716">C. apiciferum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have abdominal dark tergites without conspicuous stripes; 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Maier" authorityYear="2009" box="[1280,1441,723,745]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="716" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hidalgense">
<emphasis box="[1280,1441,723,745]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="716">C. hidalgense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the stylus with a tuft of long hairs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[826,1442,478,929]" pageId="19" pageNumber="716">
In early stages 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Maier" authorityYear="2009" box="[1027,1181,784,806]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="716" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hidalgense">
<emphasis box="[1027,1181,784,806]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="716">C. hidalgense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very distinctive and easily separated by the spicule pattern on the thorax. It is the only species of the Apiciferum group with spicules on the anterodorsal and lateral margins of the metathorax.
</paragraph>
